BFN 

  [Text] Khaskovo, April 26 (BTA) -- Customs officers at the 
Kapitan Andreevo border checkpoint (on the Bulgarian-Turkish 
border) prevented the smuggling of 24 kg of heroin, the local 
BTA correspondent reported. The drug-trafficker is a Pole 
travelling from Turkey to Poland in a BMW car. 
  The narcotic was found in 92 packets in a secret compartment 
behind the back seat of the car. 

